124        public void test0401() throws JavaScriptModelException {
125                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0401", "A.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
126                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, true);
127                ASTNode node = getASTNode((JavaScriptUnit) result, 0, 0);
128                assertNotNull(node);
129                assertTrue("Not a method declaration", node.getNodeType() == ASTNode.FUNCTION_DECLARATION); //$NON-NLS-1$
130                FunctionDeclaration methodDeclaration = (FunctionDeclaration) node;
131                Block block = methodDeclaration.getBody();
132                List statements = block.statements();
133                assertEquals("wrong size", 1, statements.size()); //$NON-NLS-1$
134                Statement statement = (Statement) statements.get(0);
135                assertTrue("Not a return statement", statement.getNodeType() == ASTNode.RETURN_STATEMENT); //$NON-NLS-1$
136                ReturnStatement returnStatement = (ReturnStatement) statement;
137                Expression expression = returnStatement.getExpression();
138                assertNotNull("there is no expression", expression); //$NON-NLS-1$
139                // call the default initialization
140                methodDeclaration.getReturnType2();
141                ITypeBinding typeBinding = expression.resolveTypeBinding();
142                assertNotNull("No typebinding", typeBinding); //$NON-NLS-1$
143                assertEquals("wrong name", "int", typeBinding.getName()); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$
144        }

149        public void test0402() throws JavaScriptModelException {
150                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0402", "A.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
151                char[] source = sourceUnit.getSource().toCharArray();

349        /**
350         * http://dev.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=23162
351         */
352        public void test0409() throws JavaScriptModelException {
353                Hashtable options = JavaScriptCore.getOptions();
354                Hashtable newOptions = JavaScriptCore.getOptions();
355                try {
356                        newOptions.put(JavaScriptCore.COMPILER_SOURCE, JavaScriptCore.VERSION_1_4);
357                        JavaScriptCore.setOptions(newOptions);
358                        IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0409", "A.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
359                        ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, true);
360                        assertTrue("Not a compilation unit", result.getNodeType() == ASTNode.JAVASCRIPT_UNIT); //$NON-NLS-1$
361                        JavaScriptUnit compilationUnit = (JavaScriptUnit) result; 
362                        assertProblemsSize(compilationUnit, 0);
363                        BindingsCollectorVisitor bindingsCollectorVisitor = new BindingsCollectorVisitor();
364                        compilationUnit.accept(bindingsCollectorVisitor);
365                        assertEquals("wrong number", 3, bindingsCollectorVisitor.getUnresolvedNodesSet().size()); //$NON-NLS-1$
366                        Map bindingsMap = bindingsCollectorVisitor.getBindingsMap();
367                        assertEquals("wrong number", 211, bindingsMap.size()); //$NON-NLS-1$
368                        ASTNodesCollectorVisitor nodesCollector = new ASTNodesCollectorVisitor();
369                        compilationUnit.accept(nodesCollector);
370                        Set detachedNodes = nodesCollector.getDetachedAstNodes();
371                        int counter = 0;
372                        for (Iterator iterator = detachedNodes.iterator(); iterator.hasNext(); ) {
373                                ASTNode detachedNode = (ASTNode) iterator.next();
374                                counter++;
375                                IBinding binding = (IBinding) bindingsMap.get(detachedNode);
376                                assertNotNull(binding);
377                                switch(detachedNode.getNodeType()) {
378                                        case ASTNode.ARRAY_ACCESS :
379                                        case ASTNode.ARRAY_CREATION :
380                                        case ASTNode.ARRAY_INITIALIZER :
381                                        case ASTNode.ASSIGNMENT :
382                                        case ASTNode.BOOLEAN_LITERAL :
383                                        case ASTNode.CAST_EXPRESSION :
384                                        case ASTNode.CHARACTER_LITERAL :
385                                        case ASTNode.CLASS_INSTANCE_CREATION :
386                                        case ASTNode.CONDITIONAL_EXPRESSION :
387                                        case ASTNode.FIELD_ACCESS :
388                                        case ASTNode.INFIX_EXPRESSION :
389                                        case ASTNode.INSTANCEOF_EXPRESSION :
390                                        case ASTNode.FUNCTION_INVOCATION :
391                                        case ASTNode.NULL_LITERAL :
392                                        case ASTNode.NUMBER_LITERAL :
393                                        case ASTNode.POSTFIX_EXPRESSION :
394                                        case ASTNode.PREFIX_EXPRESSION :
395                                        case ASTNode.THIS_EXPRESSION :
396                                        case ASTNode.TYPE_LITERAL :
397                                        case ASTNode.VARIABLE_DECLARATION_EXPRESSION :
398                                                ITypeBinding typeBinding = ((Expression) detachedNode).resolveTypeBinding();
399                                                if (!binding.equals(typeBinding)) {
400                                                        System.out.println(detachedNode);
401                                                }
402                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(typeBinding)); //$NON-NLS-1$
403                                                break;                                                
404                                        case ASTNode.VARIABLE_DECLARATION_FRAGMENT :
405                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(((VariableDeclarationFragment) detachedNode).resolveBinding())); //$NON-NLS-1$
406                                                break;                                                
407                                        case ASTNode.ANONYMOUS_CLASS_DECLARATION :
408                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(((AnonymousClassDeclaration) detachedNode).resolveBinding())); //$NON-NLS-1$
409                                                break;
410                                        case ASTNode.QUALIFIED_NAME :
411                                        case ASTNode.SIMPLE_NAME :
412                                                IBinding newBinding = ((Name) detachedNode).resolveBinding();
413                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(newBinding)); //$NON-NLS-1$
414                                                break;
415                                        case ASTNode.ARRAY_TYPE :
416                                        case ASTNode.SIMPLE_TYPE :
417                                        case ASTNode.PRIMITIVE_TYPE :
418                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(((Type) detachedNode).resolveBinding())); //$NON-NLS-1$
419                                                break;
420                                        case ASTNode.CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATION :
421                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(((ConstructorInvocation) detachedNode).resolveConstructorBinding())); //$NON-NLS-1$
422                                                break;
423                                        case ASTNode.IMPORT_DECLARATION :
424                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(((ImportDeclaration) detachedNode).resolveBinding())); //$NON-NLS-1$
425                                                break;
426                                        case ASTNode.FUNCTION_DECLARATION :
427                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(((FunctionDeclaration) detachedNode).resolveBinding())); //$NON-NLS-1$
428                                                break;
429                                        case ASTNode.PACKAGE_DECLARATION :
430                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(((PackageDeclaration) detachedNode).resolveBinding())); //$NON-NLS-1$
431                                                break;
432                                        case ASTNode.TYPE_DECLARATION :
433                                                assertTrue("binding not equals", binding.equals(((TypeDeclaration) detachedNode).resolveBinding())); //$NON-NLS-1$
434                                                break;
435                                }
436                        }
437                } finally {
438                        JavaScriptCore.setOptions(options);
439                }
440        }

760                List fragments = statement.fragments();
761                assertEquals("Wrong size", 1, fragments.size());
762                VariableDeclarationFragment fragment = (VariableDeclarationFragment) fragments.get(0);
763                Expression expression = fragment.getInitializer();
764                assertEquals("Not an infix expression", expression.getNodeType(), ASTNode.INFIX_EXPRESSION);
765                InfixExpression infixExpression = (InfixExpression) expression;
766                checkSourceRange(infixExpression, "( 1 + 2 ) + 3", source);
767                Expression expression2 = infixExpression.getLeftOperand();
768                assertEquals("Not a parenthesized expression", expression2.getNodeType(), ASTNode.PARENTHESIZED_EXPRESSION);
769                checkSourceRange(expression2, "( 1 + 2 )", source);
770                ParenthesizedExpression parenthesizedExpression = (ParenthesizedExpression) expression2;
771                Expression expression3 = parenthesizedExpression.getExpression();
772                checkSourceRange(expression3, "1 + 2", source);
773        }

1180         */
1181        public void test0440() throws JavaScriptModelException {
1182                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0440", "A.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
1183                char[] source = sourceUnit.getSource().toCharArray();
1184                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, true);
1185                assertTrue("not a compilation unit", result.getNodeType() == ASTNode.JAVASCRIPT_UNIT); //$NON-NLS-1$
1186                JavaScriptUnit unit = (JavaScriptUnit) result;
1187                assertEquals("Wrong number of problems", 0, unit.getProblems().length); //$NON-NLS-1$<
1188                ASTNode node = getASTNode(unit, 0, 0, 0);
1189                assertEquals("Not a variable declaration statement", ASTNode.VARIABLE_DECLARATION_STATEMENT, node.getNodeType());
1190                VariableDeclarationStatement statement = (VariableDeclarationStatement) node;
1191                List fragments = statement.fragments();
1192                VariableDeclarationFragment fragment = (VariableDeclarationFragment) fragments.get(0);
1193                Expression expression = fragment.getInitializer();
1194                assertEquals("Not an infix expression", ASTNode.INFIX_EXPRESSION, expression.getNodeType());
1195                // 2 * 3 + "" + (true)
1196                InfixExpression infixExpression = (InfixExpression) expression;
1197                checkSourceRange(infixExpression, "2 * 3 + \"\" + (true)", source);
1198                Expression leftOperand = infixExpression.getLeftOperand();
1199                checkSourceRange(leftOperand, "2 * 3 + \"\"", source);
1200                checkSourceRange(infixExpression.getRightOperand(), "(true)", source);
1201                assertEquals("wrong operator", infixExpression.getOperator(), InfixExpression.Operator.PLUS);
1202                assertEquals("wrong type", ASTNode.INFIX_EXPRESSION, leftOperand.getNodeType());
1203                infixExpression = (InfixExpression) leftOperand;
1204                checkSourceRange(infixExpression, "2 * 3 + \"\"", source);
1205                leftOperand = infixExpression.getLeftOperand();
1206                checkSourceRange(leftOperand, "2 * 3", source);
1207                checkSourceRange(infixExpression.getRightOperand(), "\"\"", source);
1208                assertEquals("wrong operator", infixExpression.getOperator(), InfixExpression.Operator.PLUS);
1209                assertEquals("wrong type", ASTNode.INFIX_EXPRESSION, leftOperand.getNodeType());
1210                infixExpression = (InfixExpression) leftOperand;
1211                checkSourceRange(infixExpression, "2 * 3", source);
1212                leftOperand = infixExpression.getLeftOperand();
1213                checkSourceRange(leftOperand, "2", source);
1214                checkSourceRange(infixExpression.getRightOperand(), "3", source);
1215                assertEquals("wrong operator", infixExpression.getOperator(), InfixExpression.Operator.TIMES);
1216        }

1397        public void test0450() throws JavaScriptModelException {
1398                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0450", "A.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
1399                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, true);
1400                assertTrue("not a compilation unit", result.getNodeType() == ASTNode.JAVASCRIPT_UNIT); //$NON-NLS-1$
1401                JavaScriptUnit unit = (JavaScriptUnit) result;
1402                assertEquals("Wrong number of problems", 0, unit.getProblems().length); //$NON-NLS-1$
1403                ASTNode node = getASTNode(unit, 0);
1404                assertEquals("Not a type declaration", node.getNodeType(), ASTNode.TYPE_DECLARATION);
1405                TypeDeclaration typeDeclaration = (TypeDeclaration) node;
1406                ITypeBinding typeBinding = typeDeclaration.resolveBinding();
1407                assertNotNull("No type binding", typeBinding);
1408                assertTrue("not a class", typeBinding.isClass());
1409                assertTrue("not a toplevel type", typeBinding.isTopLevel());
1410                assertTrue("a local type", !typeBinding.isLocal());
1411                assertTrue("an anonymous type", !typeBinding.isAnonymous());
1412                assertTrue("a member type", !typeBinding.isMember());
1413                assertTrue("a nested type", !typeBinding.isNested());
1414                node = getASTNode(unit, 0, 0, 0);
1415                assertEquals("Not an expression statement", node.getNodeType(), ASTNode.EXPRESSION_STATEMENT);
1416                Expression expression = ((ExpressionStatement) node).getExpression();
1417                assertEquals("Not a class instance creation", expression.getNodeType(), ASTNode.CLASS_INSTANCE_CREATION);
1418                ClassInstanceCreation classInstanceCreation = (ClassInstanceCreation) expression;
1419                AnonymousClassDeclaration anonymousClassDeclaration = classInstanceCreation.getAnonymousClassDeclaration();
1420                typeBinding = anonymousClassDeclaration.resolveBinding();
1421                assertNotNull("No type binding", typeBinding);
1422                assertTrue("not a class", typeBinding.isClass());
1423                assertTrue("a toplevel type", !typeBinding.isTopLevel());
1424                assertTrue("not a local type", typeBinding.isLocal());
1425                assertTrue("not an anonymous type", typeBinding.isAnonymous());
1426                assertTrue("a member type", !typeBinding.isMember());
1427                assertTrue("not a nested type", typeBinding.isNested());
1428                ASTNode astNode = unit.findDeclaringNode(typeBinding);
1429                assertEquals("Wrong type", ASTNode.ANONYMOUS_CLASS_DECLARATION, astNode.getNodeType());
1430                assertNotNull("Didn't get a key", typeBinding.getKey());
1431                astNode = unit.findDeclaringNode(typeBinding.getKey());
1432                assertNotNull("Didn't get a declaring node", astNode);
1433                
1434                ITypeBinding typeBinding3 = classInstanceCreation.resolveTypeBinding();
1435                assertEquals("wrong binding", typeBinding, typeBinding3);
1436                
1437                List bodyDeclarations = anonymousClassDeclaration.bodyDeclarations();
1438                assertEquals("wrong size", 2, bodyDeclarations.size());
1439                BodyDeclaration bodyDeclaration = (BodyDeclaration) bodyDeclarations.get(0);
1440                assertTrue("not a type declaration", bodyDeclaration.getNodeType() == ASTNode.TYPE_DECLARATION);
1441                typeDeclaration = (TypeDeclaration) bodyDeclaration;
1442                
1443                bodyDeclaration = (BodyDeclaration) bodyDeclarations.get(1);
1444                FunctionDeclaration methodDeclaration = (FunctionDeclaration) bodyDeclaration;
1445                Block block = methodDeclaration.getBody();
1446                assertNotNull("No body", block);
1447                List statements = block.statements();
1448                assertEquals("wrong size", 2, statements.size());
1449                Statement statement = (Statement) statements.get(1);
1450                assertEquals("Not a variable declaration statement", statement.getNodeType(), ASTNode.VARIABLE_DECLARATION_STATEMENT);
1451                VariableDeclarationStatement variableDeclarationStatement = (VariableDeclarationStatement) statement;
1452                Type type = variableDeclarationStatement.getType();
1453                assertNotNull("No type", type);
1454                
1455                ITypeBinding typeBinding2 = type.resolveBinding();
1456                typeBinding = typeDeclaration.resolveBinding();
1457                assertTrue("not equals", typeBinding == typeBinding2);
1458                assertNotNull("No type binding", typeBinding);
1459                assertTrue("not a class", typeBinding.isClass());
1460                assertTrue("a toplevel type", !typeBinding.isTopLevel());
1461                assertTrue("an anonymous type", !typeBinding.isAnonymous());
1462                assertTrue("not a member type", typeBinding.isMember());
1463                assertTrue("not a nested type", typeBinding.isNested());                
1464                assertTrue("a local type", !typeBinding.isLocal());
1465                
1466                bodyDeclarations = typeDeclaration.bodyDeclarations();
1467                assertEquals("wrong size", 1, bodyDeclarations.size());
1468                bodyDeclaration = (BodyDeclaration) bodyDeclarations.get(0);
1469                assertTrue("not a type declaration", bodyDeclaration.getNodeType() == ASTNode.TYPE_DECLARATION);
1470                typeDeclaration = (TypeDeclaration) bodyDeclaration;
1471                typeBinding = typeDeclaration.resolveBinding();
1472                assertNotNull("No type binding", typeBinding);
1473                assertTrue("not a class", typeBinding.isClass());
1474                assertTrue("a toplevel type", !typeBinding.isTopLevel());
1475                assertTrue("an anonymous type", !typeBinding.isAnonymous());
1476                assertTrue("not a member type", typeBinding.isMember());
1477                assertTrue("not a nested type", typeBinding.isNested());                
1478                assertTrue("a local type", !typeBinding.isLocal());
1479        }

1710        public void test0461() throws JavaScriptModelException {

1727                checkSourceRange(expression2, "foo().y.toList()", source);

1732                checkSourceRange(methodInvocation.getName(), "toList", source);
1733                assertTrue("not a field access", expression3.getNodeType() == ASTNode.FIELD_ACCESS);
1734                FieldAccess fieldAccess = (FieldAccess) expression3;
1735                checkSourceRange(fieldAccess.getName(), "y", source);
1736                Expression expression4 = fieldAccess.getExpression();
1737                checkSourceRange(expression4, "foo()", source);
1738                assertTrue("not a method invocation", expression4.getNodeType() == ASTNode.FUNCTION_INVOCATION);
1739                FunctionInvocation methodInvocation2 = (FunctionInvocation) expression4;
1740                checkSourceRange(methodInvocation2.getName(), "foo", source);
1741                assertNull("no null", methodInvocation2.getExpression());
1742        }

2834        public void test0499() throws JavaScriptModelException {
2835                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0499", "A.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
2836                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, true);
2837                assertTrue("not a compilation unit", result.getNodeType() == ASTNode.JAVASCRIPT_UNIT); //$NON-NLS-1$
2838                JavaScriptUnit unit = (JavaScriptUnit) result;
2839                assertEquals("Wrong number of problems", 1, unit.getProblems().length); //$NON-NLS-1$
2840                ASTNode node = getASTNode(unit, 0, 0, 1);
2841                assertNotNull(node);
2842                assertTrue("Not an expression statement", node.getNodeType() == ASTNode.EXPRESSION_STATEMENT); //$NON-NLS-1$
2843                Expression expression = ((ExpressionStatement) node).getExpression();
2844                assertTrue("Not an assignment", expression.getNodeType() == ASTNode.ASSIGNMENT); //$NON-NLS-1$
2845                Assignment assignment = (Assignment) expression;
2846                Expression expression2 = assignment.getRightHandSide();
2847                assertTrue("Not an infix expression", expression2.getNodeType() == ASTNode.INFIX_EXPRESSION); //$NON-NLS-1$
2848                InfixExpression infixExpression = (InfixExpression) expression2;
2849                Expression expression3 = infixExpression.getLeftOperand();
2850                assertTrue("Not a simple name", expression3.getNodeType() == ASTNode.SIMPLE_NAME); //$NON-NLS-1$
2851                ITypeBinding binding = expression3.resolveTypeBinding();
2852                assertNotNull("No binding", binding);
2853                Expression expression4 = assignment.getLeftHandSide();
2854                assertTrue("Not a simple name", expression4.getNodeType() == ASTNode.SIMPLE_NAME); //$NON-NLS-1$
2855                ITypeBinding binding2 = expression4.resolveTypeBinding();
2856                assertNotNull("No binding", binding2);
2857                assertTrue("Should be the same", binding == binding2);
2858        }

3426                assertTrue(declaration.subtreeMatch(new ASTMatcher(), bodyDeclaration));
3427                ASTNode root = bodyDeclaration.getRoot();

3573        /**
3574         * Ensure an OperationCanceledException is correcly thrown when progress monitor is canceled
3575         * @deprecated using deprecated code
3576         */
3577        public void test0521() throws JavaScriptModelException {
3578                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter", "src", "test0521", "A.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
3579                
3580                // count the number of time isCanceled() is called when converting this source unit
3581                WorkingCopyOwner owner = new WorkingCopyOwner() {};
3582                CancelCounter counter = new CancelCounter();
3583                ASTParser parser = ASTParser.newParser(AST.JLS2);
3584                parser.setSource(sourceUnit);
3585                parser.setResolveBindings(true);
3586                parser.setWorkingCopyOwner(owner);
3587                parser.createAST(counter);
3588                
3589                // throw an OperatonCanceledException at each point isCanceled() is called
3590                for (int i = 0; i < counter.count; i++) {
3591                        boolean gotException = false;
3592                        try {
3593                                parser = ASTParser.newParser(AST.JLS2);
3594                                parser.setSource(sourceUnit);
3595                                parser.setResolveBindings(true);
3596                                parser.setWorkingCopyOwner(owner);
3597                                parser.createAST(new Canceler(i));
3598                        } catch (OperationCanceledException e) {
3599                                gotException = true;
3600                        }
3601                        assertTrue("Should get an OperationCanceledException (" + i + ")", gotException);
3602                }
3603                
3604                // last should not throw an OperationCanceledException
3605                parser = ASTParser.newParser(AST.JLS2);
3606                parser.setSource(sourceUnit);
3607                parser.setResolveBindings(true);
3608                parser.setWorkingCopyOwner(owner);
3609                parser.createAST(new Canceler(counter.count));
3610        }

4453        public void test0541() throws JavaScriptModelException {

4459                assertEquals("not a field declaration", ASTNode.FIELD_DECLARATION, node.getNodeType());
4460                class Change14FieldAccessASTVisitor extends ASTVisitor {
4461                        int counter;
4462                        Change14FieldAccessASTVisitor() {
4463                                counter = 0;
4464                        }
4465                        public void endVisit(QualifiedName qualifiedName) {
4466                                IBinding i_binding = qualifiedName.getQualifier().resolveBinding();                                                
4467                                ITypeBinding type_binding = qualifiedName.getQualifier().resolveTypeBinding();
4468                                if (i_binding == null || type_binding == null) {
4469                                        counter++;
4470                                }
4471                        }
4472                }
4473                Change14FieldAccessASTVisitor visitor = new Change14FieldAccessASTVisitor();
4474                unit.accept(visitor);
4475                assertEquals("Missing binding", 0, visitor.counter);
4476        }

4836                TypeDeclaration declaration = (TypeDeclaration) result.types().get(0);
4837                Block body = declaration.getMethods()[0].getBody();
4838                ExpressionStatement expr = (ExpressionStatement) body.statements().get(0);
4839                FunctionInvocation invocation = (FunctionInvocation) expr.getExpression();
4840                InfixExpression node = (InfixExpression) invocation.arguments().get(0);
4841                ITypeBinding typeBinding = node.resolveTypeBinding();
4842                assertEquals("wrong type", "java.lang.String", typeBinding.getQualifiedName());
4843                checkSourceRange(node, "\"a\" + \"a\" + \"a\"", source);
4844                List extendedOperands = node.extendedOperands();
4845                assertEquals("Wrong size", 1, extendedOperands.size());
4846                Expression leftOperand = node.getLeftOperand();
4847                checkSourceRange(leftOperand, "\"a\"", source);
4848                typeBinding = leftOperand.resolveTypeBinding();
4849                assertEquals("wrong type", "java.lang.String", typeBinding.getQualifiedName());
4850                Expression rightOperand = node.getRightOperand();
4851                checkSourceRange(rightOperand, "\"a\"", source);
4852                typeBinding = rightOperand.resolveTypeBinding();
4853                assertEquals("wrong type", "java.lang.String", typeBinding.getQualifiedName());
4854                Expression expression = (Expression) extendedOperands.get(0);
4855                checkSourceRange(expression, "\"a\"", source);
4856                typeBinding = expression.resolveTypeBinding();
4857                assertEquals("wrong type", "java.lang.String", typeBinding.getQualifiedName());
4858        }

5376        /**
5377         * https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=77645
5378         */
5379        public void test0578() throws JavaScriptModelException {
5380                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter", "src", "test0578", "X.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
5381                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, true);
5382                assertEquals("not a compilation unit", ASTNode.JAVASCRIPT_UNIT, result.getNodeType()); //$NON-NLS-1$
5383                JavaScriptUnit unit = (JavaScriptUnit) result;
5384                assertProblemsSize(unit, 0);
5385                unit.accept(new ASTVisitor() {
5386                        /* (non-Javadoc)
5387                         * @see org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor#visit(org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.SingleVariableDeclaration)
5388                         */
5389                        public boolean visit(SingleVariableDeclaration node) {
5390                                IVariableBinding binding = node.resolveBinding();
5391                                assertNotNull("No method", binding.getDeclaringMethod());
5392                                return false;
5393                        }
5394                        /* (non-Javadoc)
5395                         * @see org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor#visit(org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.VariableDeclarationFragment)
5396                         */
5397                        public boolean visit(VariableDeclarationFragment node) {
5398                                IVariableBinding binding = node.resolveBinding();
5399                                ASTNode parent = node.getParent();
5400                                if (parent != null && binding != null) {
5401                                        final IFunctionBinding declaringMethod = binding.getDeclaringMethod();
5402                                        final String variableBindingName = binding.getName();
5403                                        switch(parent.getNodeType()) {
5404                                                case ASTNode.FIELD_DECLARATION :
5405                                                        assertNull("Got a method", declaringMethod);
5406                                                        break;
5407                                                default :
5408                                                        if (variableBindingName.equals("var1")
5409                                                                        || variableBindingName.equals("var2")) {
5410                                                                assertNull("Got a method", declaringMethod);
5411                                                        } else {
5412                                                                assertNotNull("No method", declaringMethod);
5413                                                                String methodName = declaringMethod.getName();
5414                                                                if (variableBindingName.equals("var4")) {
5415                                                                        assertEquals("Wrong method", "foo", methodName);
5416                                                                } else if (variableBindingName.equals("var5")) {
5417                                                                        assertEquals("Wrong method", "foo2", methodName);
5418                                                                } else if (variableBindingName.equals("var7")) {
5419                                                                        assertEquals("Wrong method", "foo3", methodName);
5420                                                                } else if (variableBindingName.equals("var8")) {
5421                                                                        assertEquals("Wrong method", "X", methodName);
5422                                                                } else if (variableBindingName.equals("var9")) {
5423                                                                        assertEquals("Wrong method", "bar3", methodName);
5424                                                                } else if (variableBindingName.equals("var10")) {
5425                                                                        assertEquals("Wrong method", "bar3", methodName);
5426                                                                } else if (variableBindingName.equals("var11")) {
5427                                                                        assertEquals("Wrong method", "X", methodName);
5428                                                                } 
5429                                                        }
5430                                        }
5431                                }
5432                                return false;
5433                        }
5434                        /* (non-Javadoc)
5435                         * @see org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor#visit(org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.FieldAccess)
5436                         */
5437                        public boolean visit(FieldAccess node) {
5438                                IVariableBinding binding = node.resolveFieldBinding();
5439                                assertNull("No method", binding.getDeclaringMethod());
5440                                return false;
5441                        }
5442                        /* (non-Javadoc)
5443                         * @see org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor#endVisit(org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.SuperFieldAccess)
5444                         */
5445                        public boolean visit(SuperFieldAccess node) {
5446                                IVariableBinding binding = node.resolveFieldBinding();
5447                                assertNull("No method", binding.getDeclaringMethod());
5448                                return false;
5449                        }
5450                });
5451        }

5477                        "        d String[][]tab;\n" +
5478                        "}";
5479                        ASTNode node = buildAST(
5480                                source,
5481                                workingCopy,
5482                                false);
5483                        assertEquals("wrong type", ASTNode.JAVASCRIPT_UNIT, node.getNodeType());
5484                        JavaScriptUnit compilationUnit = (JavaScriptUnit) node;
5485                        node = getASTNode(compilationUnit, 0, 0);
5486                        assertEquals("wrong type", ASTNode.FIELD_DECLARATION, node.getNodeType());
5487                        FieldDeclaration fieldDeclaration = (FieldDeclaration) node;
5488                        checkSourceRange(fieldDeclaration, "d String[][]", source.toCharArray());
5489                        Type type = fieldDeclaration.getType();
5490                        assertTrue("Not a simple type", type.isSimpleType());
5491                        List fragments = fieldDeclaration.fragments();
5492                        assertEquals("Wrong size", 1, fragments.size());
5493                        VariableDeclarationFragment fragment = (VariableDeclarationFragment) fragments.get(0);
5494                        assertEquals("Wrong extended dimensions", 2, fragment.getExtraDimensions());
5495                } finally {
5496                        if (workingCopy != null)
5497                                workingCopy.discardWorkingCopy();
5498                }
5499        }

6850                        unit.accept(new ASTVisitor() {
6851                                public boolean visit(CharacterLiteral characterLiteral) {
6852                                        try {
6853                                                final String escapedValue = characterLiteral.getEscapedValue();
6854                                                final char charValue = characterLiteral.charValue();
6855                                                if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\0\'")) {
6856                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 0, charValue);
6857                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\1\'")) {
6858                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 1, charValue);
6859                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\2\'")) {
6860                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 2, charValue);
6861                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\3\'")) {
6862                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 3, charValue);
6863                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\4\'")) {
6864                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 4, charValue);
6865                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\5\'")) {
6866                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 5, charValue);
6867                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\6\'")) {
6868                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 6, charValue);
6869                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\7\'")) {
6870                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 7, charValue);
6871                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\077\'")) {
6872                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 63, charValue);
6873                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\55\'")) {
6874                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 45, charValue);
6875                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\77\'")) {
6876                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 63, charValue);
6877                                                } else if (escapedValue.equals("\'\\377\'")) {
6878                                                        assertEquals("Wrong value", 255, charValue);
6879                                                } else {
6880                                                        assertTrue("Should not get there", false);
6881                                                }
6882                                        } catch(IllegalArgumentException e) {
6883                                                assertTrue("Should not happen", false);
6884                                        }
6885                                        return false;
6886                                }
6887                        });
6888                } finally {
6889                        if (workingCopy != null)
6890                                workingCopy.discardWorkingCopy();
6891                }
6892        }

7012                                        return false;

7018                        });

7137                        assertEquals("Wrong size", 1, bodyDeclarations.size());
7138                        BodyDeclaration bodyDeclaration = (BodyDeclaration) bodyDeclarations.get(0);
7139                        assertEquals("Not a method declaration", ASTNode.FUNCTION_DECLARATION, bodyDeclaration.getNodeType());
7140                        FunctionDeclaration methodDeclaration = (FunctionDeclaration) bodyDeclaration;
7141                        IFunctionBinding methodBinding = methodDeclaration.resolveBinding();
7142                        
7143                        node = getASTNode(unit, 0, 0, 2);

7150                        assertEquals("Wrong size", 1, bodyDeclarations.size());

7157                } finally {

7559        
7560        /*
7561         * Ensures that 2 type bindings (one from .class file, the other from attache source) are "isEqualTo(...)".
7562         * (regression test for bug 130317 ASTParser with IClassFile as source creates type bindings that are not isEqualTo(..) binary bindings)
7563         */
7564        public void test0641() throws JavaScriptModelException {
7565                // Integer from attached source
7566                IClassFile classFile = getClassFile("Converter", getConverterJCLPath().toOSString(), "java.lang", "Integer.class");
7567                String source = classFile.getSource();
7568                MarkerInfo markerInfo = new MarkerInfo(source);
7569                markerInfo.astStarts = new int[] {source.indexOf("public")};
7570                markerInfo.astEnds = new int[] {source.lastIndexOf('}') + 1};
7571                ASTNode node = buildAST(markerInfo, classFile);
7572                IBinding bindingFromAttachedSource = ((TypeDeclaration) node).resolveBinding();                
7573                
7574                IJavaScriptUnit workingCopy = null;
7575                try {
7576                    workingCopy = getWorkingCopy("/Converter/src/X.js", true/*resolve*/);
7577                    String contents =
7578                                "public class X {\n" + 
7579                                "        /*start*/Integer/*end*/ field;\n" + 
7580                                "}";
7581                           IBinding[] bindings = resolveBindings(contents, workingCopy);
7582                           assertTrue("2 type bindings should be equals", bindingFromAttachedSource.isEqualTo(bindings[0]));
7583                } finally {
7584                        if (workingCopy != null)
7585                                workingCopy.discardWorkingCopy();
7586                }
7587        }

8029        public void test0654() throws JavaScriptModelException {

8033                                "public class X {\n" +
8034                                "        int i;\n" +
8035                                "        public void foo(int[] a) {\n" + 
8036                                "        }\n" + 
8037                                "        String s;\n" +
8038                                "        public String[][] bar() {\n" + 
8039                                "                return null;\n" +
8040                                "        }\n" + 
8041                                "}";
8042                        workingCopy = getWorkingCopy("/Converter/src/X.js", true/*resolve*/);
8043                        ASTNode node = buildAST(
8044                                contents,
8045                                workingCopy,
8046                                false,
8047                                true);
8048                        assertEquals("Not a compilation unit", ASTNode.JAVASCRIPT_UNIT, node.getNodeType());
8049                        JavaScriptUnit unit = (JavaScriptUnit) node;
8050                        assertProblemsSize(unit, 0);
8051                        node = getASTNode(unit, 0, 0);
8052                        assertEquals("Not a field declaration", ASTNode.FIELD_DECLARATION, node.getNodeType());
8053                        FieldDeclaration declaration = (FieldDeclaration) node;
8054                        Type type = declaration.getType();
8055                        ITypeBinding typeBinding = type.resolveBinding();
8056                        assertTrue("Not a primitive type", typeBinding.isPrimitive());
8057                        assertEquals("Not int", "int", typeBinding.getName());
8058                        try {
8059                                typeBinding.createArrayType(-1);
8060                                assertTrue("Should throw an exception", false);
8061                        } catch(IllegalArgumentException exception) {
8062                                // ignore
8063                        }
8064                        try {
8065                                typeBinding.createArrayType(0);
8066                                assertTrue("Should throw an exception", false);
8067                        } catch(IllegalArgumentException exception) {
8068                                // ignore
8069                        }
8070                        try {
8071                                typeBinding.createArrayType(256);
8072                                assertTrue("Should throw an exception", false);
8073                        } catch(IllegalArgumentException exception) {
8074                                // ignore
8075                        }
8076                        ITypeBinding binding = typeBinding.createArrayType(2);
8077                        assertEquals("Wrong dimensions", 2, binding.getDimensions());
8078                        assertTrue("Not an array type binding", binding.isArray());
8079                        ITypeBinding componentType = binding.getComponentType();
8080                        assertTrue("Not an array type binding", componentType.isArray());
8081                        assertEquals("Wrong dimensions", 1, componentType.getDimensions());
8082                        componentType = componentType.getComponentType();
8083                        assertFalse("An array type binding", componentType.isArray());
8084                        assertEquals("Wrong dimensions", 0, componentType.getDimensions());
8085                        
8086                        binding = typeBinding.createArrayType(1);
8087                        node = getASTNode(unit, 0, 1);
8088                        assertEquals("Not a method declaration", ASTNode.FUNCTION_DECLARATION, node.getNodeType());
8089                        FunctionDeclaration methodDeclaration = (FunctionDeclaration) node;
8090                        List parameters = methodDeclaration.parameters();
8091                        assertEquals("Wrong size", 1, parameters.size());
8092                        SingleVariableDeclaration parameter = (SingleVariableDeclaration) parameters.get(0);
8093                        Type type2 = parameter.getType();
8094                        ITypeBinding typeBinding2 = type2.resolveBinding();
8095                        assertNotNull("No binding", typeBinding2);
8096                        assertTrue("Not an array binding", typeBinding2.isArray());
8097                        assertEquals("Wrong dimension", 1, typeBinding2.getDimensions());
8098                        assertEquals("Wrong type", "int", typeBinding2.getElementType().getName());
8099                        assertTrue("Should be equals", binding == typeBinding2);
8100                        
8101                        binding = typeBinding2.createArrayType(3);
8102                        assertTrue("Not an array binding", binding.isArray());
8103                        assertEquals("Wrong dimension", 4, binding.getDimensions());
8104 
8105                        node = getASTNode(unit, 0, 2);
8106                        assertEquals("Not a field declaration", ASTNode.FIELD_DECLARATION, node.getNodeType());
8107                        declaration = (FieldDeclaration) node;
8108                        type = declaration.getType();
8109                        typeBinding = type.resolveBinding();
8110                        assertTrue("A primitive type", !typeBinding.isPrimitive());
8111                        assertEquals("Not String", "String", typeBinding.getName());
8112 
8113                        binding = typeBinding.createArrayType(1);
8114                        node = getASTNode(unit, 0, 3);
8115                        assertEquals("Not a method declaration", ASTNode.FUNCTION_DECLARATION, node.getNodeType());
8116                        methodDeclaration = (FunctionDeclaration) node;
8117                        type = methodDeclaration.getReturnType2();
8118                        assertNotNull("No return type", type);
8119                        typeBinding2 = type.resolveBinding();
8120                        assertNotNull("No binding", typeBinding2);
8121                        assertTrue("Not an array binding", typeBinding2.isArray());
8122                        assertEquals("Wrong dimension", 2, typeBinding2.getDimensions());
8123                        assertEquals("Wrong type", "String", typeBinding2.getElementType().getName());
8124                        typeBinding2 = typeBinding2.getComponentType();
8125                        assertTrue("Not an array binding", typeBinding2.isArray());
8126                        assertEquals("Wrong dimension", 1, typeBinding2.getDimensions());
8127                        assertTrue("Should be equals", binding == typeBinding2);
8128                } finally {
8129                        if (workingCopy != null)
8130                                workingCopy.discardWorkingCopy();
8131                }
8132        }
